node.text:
IT'S THE NPS-AVERSARY!
From the early days of "hey, maybe we should keep this place wild", through pivotal moments of the very fabric of modern American history, the NPS continues to protect and preserve the places that make us who we are. 
Today marks 103 years of National Parks Service – we think a toast is in order! Video by @maxeyfish #radparks #findyourpark

node.title: The (unofficial) History of the National Parks

node.text:
✨Leave It Better GIVEAWAY✨

Our mission is to leave it better than we found it, whether that’s a trail restoration at a national park, invasive species removal at a state park, or simply picking up at our favorite local spot. We want to spread the message and encourage our community to organize a clean up of their own, so all this week, each purchase comes with a free leave it better than you found it kit. What’s better than cleaning up? A chance to win a $200 bundles of Parks Project stuff!

How to enter:
💸 Make any purchase to receive your kit
🌳 Visit a local area and put your clean up kit to use
📸 Photograph yourself using your kit, post on your IG account and tag @parksproject to enter

Leave It Better Than You Found It Kits will be gifted with every purchase from 8/23 to 8/28. Submissions will be accepted until 9/7. Winners will be chosen on 9/7. Good luck 🤞

node.text: We worked with photographer Tommy Corey (@twerkinthedirt) and outdoor enthusiast @KamRedlawsk on a project that exemplifies what we believe in: parks are for all. Kam’s story is unique to her, but represents the kind of voices we think are essential to the outdoor community. Here's a sneak peek! #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project in North Cascades National Park with @parksproject, @ncascadesnps, and @thenomadicdrifter. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Let's talk backpacking! @ncascadesnps is the perfect place to get some mountaineering in, whether you're going on an overnight trip or a week long excursion. When exploring in the backcountry, it's important to follow all rules and regulations of the park, including fire restrictions and camping in designated sites along the trail corridor when available. Been backpacking in North Cascades National Park? Share your story with us in the comments!

Photo by @thenomadicdrifter
📍Photo taken on Nlaka'pamux and Sauk Suiattle native lands. #radparks #findyourpark #leaveitbetter

Notice: While we continue to share photos and stories from the wild lands we love, keep in mind, every park has different opening dates and restrictions. Be sure you are following all local, state, and federal guidelines.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Parks Project on August 18, 2021 tagging @equatorcoffees, and @parksproject. May be an image of one or more people, people standing, outdoors and tree.

node.text:
We teamed up with @equatorcoffees to create a special sweatshirt celebrating their newest  Equator location—Roundhouse Cafe!

Anyone who knows us knows we started Parks Project to leave the world better than we found it. Same goes for Equator Coffees—that’s why we've created this limited edition sweatshirt featuring San Francisco favorites 🌉 They are vintage cut, crazy comfortable, and the perfect weight for those days when the fog rolls in thicker than cappuccino foam.

We only made a few, and they’re going fast. Head over to the Equator store now to get yours while you can. #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Parks Project in Grand Teton National Park with @dakotalevy13, @parksproject, and @grandtetonnps. May be an image of flower and nature.

node.text:
We'd recognize these peaks anywhere 😍 Wildflowers are a common sight throughout the summer season in @grandtetonnps 🌼 Remember to always practice Leave No Trace principles when visiting, and do not collect or harvest flowers from parklands. What's your favorite Wyoming wildflower? #leaveitbetter #radparks #findyourpark #wildflowerwednesday

Photo by @dakotalevy13
📍Photo taken on Shoshone-Bannock, Eastern Shoshone, and Cheyenne native lands.
